President Obama had a video teleconference with President Karzai of Afghanistan to discuss various issues. They talked about the transition of operational lead from coalition to Afghan security forces, Afghan-led reconciliation efforts, preparations for Afghanistan's 2014 elections, and the negotiation of a Bilateral Security Agreement. They also discussed the importance of an Afghan-led and Afghan-owned peace and reconciliation process, as well as their support for an office in Doha for negotiations between the High Peace Council and authorized representatives of the Taliban. President Karzai updated President Obama on the preparations for Afghanistan's 2014 elections. They both emphasized the importance of free, fair, and credible elections for Afghanistan's future.